Today’s Cabinet secretaries are arguably the most explicitly empowered cohort in Kenya’s Executive history.Our Cabinet secretaries are formidably installed in the heart of Kenya’s official VIP culture as veritable demigods; they lack for nothing. We are not doing well at all. A limping economy starting to stagger ominously on the brink of implosion. Debt. A relentless, rampaging and devastating Covid-19 pandemic. The youth unemployment time-bomb. Corruption.
Official cluelessness and heartlessness. A friend from Baragoi advised me that over there, if a swift messenger calls on the leader of the warriors and whispers, “iko shida manyatta,” matters are exceedingly out of hand.



