In any event, they speak a language that is patronising to the point of infantilising. There is a whole industry of busybodies viciously embarked on self-assigned missions to protect the President, demand respect and exact political revenge on his behalf. Awkwardly enough, none of them is as zealous in advancing the Big 4 Agenda or ensuring administrative coherence.
Kemsa paid a “passer-by”Sh180 million, but there was no money to keep Dr Stephen Mogusu safe from infection, treat him or pay his salary. It is said by public policy theorists that government failure is just a series of principal-agent problems. This is where we find ourselves.



